Detailed Description

A queue protocol with methods for FIFO ("First In, First Out") operations.

A queue is commonly compared to waiting in line. When objects are added, they go to the back of the line, and objects are always removed from the front of the line. These actions are accomplished using -addObject: and -removeFirstObject, respectively. The frontmost object may be examined (not removed) using -firstObject.

CHStack

- (BOOL) isEqualToQueue: (id< CHQueue >)  otherQueue

Compares the receiving queue to another queue.

Two queues have equal contents if they each hold the same number of objects and objects at a given position in each queue satisfy the -isEqual: test.

Parameters:
otherQueueA queue.
Returns:
YES if the contents of otherQueue are equal to the contents of the receiver, otherwise NO.

Reimplemented in CHCircularBufferQueue, and CHListQueue.

- (NSEnumerator*) objectEnumerator

Returns an enumerator that accesses each object in the queue from front to back.

Returns:
An enumerator that accesses each object in the queue from front to back. The enumerator returned is never nil; if the queue is empty, the enumerator will always return nil for -nextObject and an empty array for -allObjects.
Attention:
The enumerator retains the collection. Once all objects in the enumerator have been consumed, the collection is released.
Warning:
Modifying a collection while it is being enumerated is unsafe, and may cause a mutation exception to be raised.
See also:
- allObjects
- (NSArray*) objectsAtIndexes: (NSIndexSet *)  indexes

Returns an array containing the objects in the receiver at the indexes specified by a given index set.

Parameters:
indexesA set of positions corresponding to objects to retrieve from the receiver.
Returns:
A new array containing the objects in the receiver specified by indexes.
Exceptions:
NSRangeExceptionif any location in indexes exceeds the bounds of the receiver.
NSInvalidArgumentExceptionif indexes is nil.
Attention:
To retrieve objects in a given NSRange, pass [NSIndexSet indexSetWithIndexesInRange:range] as the parameter to this method.

Remove all occurrences of anObject, matched using isEqual:.
